all in number, we will keep the fight and be loyal to each other.<br>
<br>
The guild leader will only be a 'title' symbol. The guild leader title is nothing more than a 'head officer'. The guild leader will settle disputes as best he/she can using officer input as his/her guide. If an officer vote results in a tie, the guild leader will have the deciding vote if it comes to that. Other than that, the guild leader's role is the same as the officer's roles.<br>
<br>
The officers' roles are to encourage member participation in guild events, but not to force members to do these things if they don't wish to. Encourage, not strongarm. Also, the officers should encourage new membership via grouping with potential members or at the very least chatting with prospective members before giving them membership.<br>
<br>
Members should have fun. That goes for officers and guild leaders alike. That is the PRIMARY rule for ANY Sanguis member.<br>
<br>
Membership: Membership should be on a 'sponsorship' basis. Someone already in Sanguis should speak highly of a prospective member, whether as an RL friend, groupmate in EQ, or otherwise. This will ensure that Sanguis members will gel with the rest of the guildmates, or at least hopefully so.<br>
<br>
Officership is earned through meritorious deeds done for Sanguis and for others. Going above and beyond the call of guildmates and others is the way to attain officership in Sanguis. Founding members of Sanguis are given officership due to their unwavering loyalty to this guild.<br>
